        {
            "type": "h2-post",
            "content": "Introduction"
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": "The <b><i>Perfekt</i></b> tense in German, equivalent to the present perfect tense in English, is used to describe actions that have been completed in the past and have relevance to the present. It is commonly used in spoken German and informal writing."
        },
        {
            "type": "callout",
            "content": "The <i>Perfekt</i> tense in German is used more frequently than in languages like English, where the Simple Past tense is primarily used in written contexts."
        },
        {
            "type": "h2",
            "content": "Usage"
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": "We use the <i>Perfekt</i> tense to express:"
        },
        {
            "type": "list",
            "itemsList": {
                "items": [
                    {
                        "text": "Describing a completed action with present relevance:",
                        "example": {
                            "audio": "Ich habe gestern einen Film gesehen",
                            "text": "Example: Ich $__habe-haben[verb-link-hover]__$ gestern einen Film $__gesehen-sehen[verb-link-hover]__$",
                            "translation": "(I watched a movie yesterday)"
                        }
                    },
                    {
                        "text": "Indicating a change of location or state:",
                        "example": {
                            "audio": "Er ist nach Berlin gefahren.",
                            "text": "Example: Er $__ist-sein[verb-link-hover]__$ nach Berlin $__gefahren-fahren[verb-link-hover]__$.",
                            "translation": "(He went to Berlin)"
                        }
                    },
                    {
                        "text": "Talking about an experience:",
                        "example": {
                            "audio": "Sie hat in Frankreich gelebt.",
                            "text": "Example: Sie $__hat-haben[verb-link-hover]__$ in Frankreich $__gelebt-leben[verb-link-hover]__$.",
                            "translation": "(She has lived in France)"
                        }
                    },
                                        {
                        "text": "Expressing a past action with a visible result:",
                        "example": {
                            "audio": "Er hat das Fenster geöffnet.",
                            "text": "Example: Er $__hat-haben[verb-link-hover]__$ das Fenster $__geöffnet-öffnen[verb-link-hover]__$.",
                            "translation": "(He has opened the window)"
                        }
                    }
                ]
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "h2",
            "content": "Conjugation"
        },
        {
            "type": "html",
            "content": "<p>The Perfekt tense is formed using two components:</p><ol><li>The <b data-verb-stem>auxiliary verb</b> (either '$__haben-haben[verb-link-hover]__$' or '$__sein-sein[verb-link-hover]__$') conjugated in the <b>present tense</b>.</li><li>The <b data-verb-prefix><i>Partizip II</i></b> of the <b>main verb.</b></li>"
        },
        {
            "type": "image",
            "image": {
                "src": "/img/lessons/perfekt-formation.svg",
