            }
        },
        {
            "type": "h3",
            "content": "Word order"
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": "In main clauses, the auxiliary verb is in the second position, and the past participle is at the end of the sentence."
        },
        {
            "type": "image",
            "image": {
                "src": "/img/lessons/perfekt-word-order.svg",
                "alt": "german Perkect tense conjugation",
                "height": 110,
